---
description: App-wide flutter gen-l10n with ARB files and LocaleCubit
globs: lib/l10n/**/*,lib/**/*.dart,l10n.yaml
alwaysApply: false
---
### Flutter localization

#### Packages
- Use `flutter_localizations` (SDK) and `intl` (version resolved by the Flutter SDK — do not hard-pin a conflicting version)

```yaml
dependencies:
  flutter_localizations:
    sdk: flutter
  intl: any
```

#### Single source of strings (required)
- Store all UI strings in root ARB files under `lib/l10n/` (e.g. `app_en.arb`, `app_fa.arb`)
- Do **not** create per-feature localization classes (`LoginLocalizations`, etc.)
- Use `flutter gen-l10n` / the generated `AppLocalizations` class only
- Access strings with `AppLocalizations.of(context).someKey` (never `Localizations.of(context, AppLocalizations)`)
- Never hardcode UI strings; put non-translatable values in `lib/core/constants.dart`

#### l10n.yaml
```yaml
arb-dir: lib/l10n
template-arb-file: app_en.arb
output-localization-file: app_localizations.dart
output-class: AppLocalizations
nullable-getter: false
```

#### ARB metadata (not JSON comments)
```json
{
  "@@locale": "en",
  "loginButton": "Login",
  "@loginButton": {
    "description": "Primary login button label on the login page"
  }
}
```

#### Runtime locale
- Manage locale with `LocaleCubit` (or Bloc)
- Register `LocaleCubit` with `registerLazySingleton` (app-wide)
- Persist the selected locale (e.g. `shared_preferences`)
- Wire `MaterialApp.locale` / `supportedLocales` / `localizationsDelegates` from that cubit
- Support RTL via Flutter's directionality when using `fa`, `ar`, etc.
